               <floruit notBefore="1300" notAfter="1455">It is the name of a representative of the 
                  <persName ref="PRS1426Adkama">ʾAdkama</persName> kingship, rulers of 
                  <placeName ref="LOC5575Saraye">Sarāye</placeName> during the 14th and 15th century, 
                  who was active in <date>1455</date>. 
                  He contributed to the construction of the monastery of 
                  <placeName ref="LOC2362DabraS">Dabra Ṣǝge</placeName>, established by the monk of 
                  <persName ref="PRS10445Yonaso">Yonās of Bur</persName>. 
                  In <date>1489</date> his name was also associated with the foundation of the
                  second monastery of  the same <persName ref="PRS10445Yonaso">Yonās of Bur</persName>, 
                  <placeName ref="LOC2257DabraD">Dabra Dǝḫuḫan</placeName>. </floruit>
                  
